# Cursor Rules System Configuration

## Overview

This directory contains the rule configurations and triggers that enforce our agile workflow and role-based communication system. The rules are automatically loaded at the start of each Cursor session and ensure consistent process execution across all projects.

## Directory Structure

```
.cursor/rules/
├── agile-framework.mdc           # Core agile framework definition
├── system/
│   ├── 100-communication-protocol.mdc    # Role communication standards
│   ├── 102-default-role-behavior.mdc     # Default role behaviors
│   ├── 103-visual-identity.mdc       # Visual identity system for roles
│   ├── 200-command-execution.mdc       # Command Execution Protocol
│   ├── 107-triggers.mdc                  # System triggers definition
│   └── ...
├── roles/                       # Role-specific rules and knowledge
└── shared/                      # Shared resources and patterns
```

## Configuration Files

### .cursorrc
Located in the root directory, this file configures:
- Automatic rule loading
- Role validation
- Immediate execution requirements
- Editor settings
- Terminal configuration

### System Triggers (107-triggers.mdc)
Defines triggers for:
- Role activation and communication
